reviewText: 5 minutes in and here comes the PC vulgarity that all "modern" stand up comics feel is mandatory these days. What a shame because she seems talented. The really "funny" thing to ME is that if I were to write the specific words used  the vulgar jokes right here  in this review, Amazon would 100% for sure censor or delete my review. No THAT fact --- to ME -- is what truly Funny here (it sure as heck isn't this video)!

Hilarious! Couldn't stop laughing the whole standup perform :-) Heather McDonald is a great author and comedian Brava to this performance. If there's a digital version as soon and audio from the Mp3 store, I will definitely buy that also . I miss you Chazan McDonald's and I have both reports physical and Kindle versions and the audiobooks for my Kindle when I'm on the road I can listen to have a good laugh while on the road :-)
The show was great.  Heather is so funny we were laughing out loud

Well, maybe her act is "geared towards women" as others have said, in a somewhat derogatory manner....no matter - I am a woman and I LOVE her act!!!! I find her funny AND likable/relatable. Her comedy isn't of the "crazy slut stories" variety- she is a semi-normal wife and mom sharing her experiences. She tells stories, is charismatic, has a unique perspective, and seems like an actually nice person. I find her so hilarious!!!
Her comedy is more geared toward women. If you like the long drawn out version of a joke then this will be for you.
I usually try to provide some context, but this woman is dry, vulgar (without the ability to contextualize) and totally predictable.  Just hollow garbage that you can do without.
